frameDefinitions: An Entity ends up in a Final_category, Final_situation, or Final_quality which it was not in before.
An Entity ends up with some Final_quality--a new fact about the Entity.
An Entity develops from a Prior_state to a Post_state.
A Claimant asserts his or her right to possession of a piece of Property (either real, such as land, or private).
An Entity comes into existence at a particular Place and Time which may take a certain Duration_of_endstate, have a Cause, or be formed from Components.
An Entity ends up with a particular new Final_quality.
frameExamples: The King <t>claims</t> this land and surrounding waters.
